
@h1 Using a timer synchronously

This tutorial introduces Felix async I/O by showing how to perform a
blocking wait on a timer.

@felix
include "std/io/faio";
var clock = #Faio::mk_alarm_clock;
Faio::sleep (clock, 5.0);
println$ "Hello world!";
@
The build command I'm using for this is,
<pre>
build/release/host/bin/flx \
   --test=build/release src/web/async_01.fdoc \
   --target-dir=build/release --target-bin=host
</pre>
